57 may hire employees as necessary to effectuate the purposes of
58 this chapter. The number of employees, their compensation, and
59 other expenditures of the committee shall be within the limits
60 and in compliance with the appropriation made therefor by the
61 Legislature and within budgets that shall be approved from
62 time to time by the commission.
63 §29-2B-3
64 (a) There is hereby established the Alabama Commission
65 on the Evaluation of Services Fund in the State Treasury for
66 the deposit of all funds received by the commission.
67 (b) The commission may receive state appropriations and
68 apply for and receive grant funds from other sources
69 including, but not limited to, foundations, governmental
70 entities, federal grants, and businesses. No public monies
71 shall be expended by the director for any purpose unless the
72 monies have been appropriated by the Legislature to the
73 commission. Any monies appropriated shall be budgeted and
74 allotted pursuant to the Budget Management Act in accordance
75 with Article 4 of Chapter 4 of Title 41, and only in the
76 amounts provided by the Legislature in the general
77 appropriations act or other appropriation acts.
78 §29-2B-4
79 (a) Any department, agency, institution, and
80 establishment of the executive branch of government and
81 regulatory agency or regulatory commission of the state,
82 excluding entities that do not receive a direct appropriation
83 from the State General Fund or the Education Trust Fund, shall
84 furnish to the commission any available material, subject to
