253 (4) Limitations of the analysis; and
254 (5) Implications for policy design or implementation,
255 if applicable.
256 (g) Upon completion, the Alabama Commission on the
257 Evaluation of Services shall publish the preliminary study
258 report on the agency's website and submit the report to the
259 Senate Finance and Taxation Committees, the House Ways and
260 Means Committees, the Legislative Committee on the Evaluation
261 of Services, and the Legislative Fiscal Officer.
262 §29-2B-11
263 The commission shall adopt rules necessary to implement
264 this chapter pursuant to the Alabama Administrative Procedure
265 Act, Chapter 22 of Title 41.
266 §29-2B-12
267 (a) There is hereby created a continuing legislative
268 committee to be known as the Legislative Committee on the
269 Evaluation of Services to exercise general supervision and
270 control over the actions of the Alabama Commission on the
271 Evaluation of Services.
